Description: Guaranteed money back if you don’t like it! (Minus shipping) This is a part caster completed by Pete Skermetta out of Austin, Texas. He’s worked for Santa Cruz in California, Waterloo in Texas, and is the current owner of Rocket Science guitar repair in Austin, Texas. Pete is known for his fret work, and this guitar reflects that. Neck: allparts/fender Vintage Style Maple Guitar Neck RELIC 100% Nitrocellulose Finish. Frets have been replaced with stainless steel wire, leveled, crowned and polished, for easy play ability. Made to match the specifications of a vintage build. Fitted with a Graphtech Nut, for modern action and tone. Adjustable truss rod (at heel) 21 Medium Nickel Silver Frets (079" x .043) 25.5 scale length 2 3/16 heel width 9.5 Radius C rear profile (Neck thickness .85 at first fret .95 at twelfth fret) 1 5/8 Graphtech nut Made from Canadian Hard rock Maple Body: VTT double bound body Heavily relic Checking in front/back under the sealer Light (body weighs 3lbs, whole guitar is 6lbs 4oz Tuners: Gotoh Vintage Bridge: Gotoh Vintage Neck pickup: LOLLARTRON HUMBUCKER Using a 1960s-era Gretsch Country Gentleman as a benchmark, we crafted this pickup to capture the classic rockabilly humbucker tone first made famous by Chet Atkins. The neck pickup is warm and buttery with a crystal clear top end. The bridge pickup is fat and twangy with a rich low end and outstanding clarity. When combined, you get the sparkle, spank, and punch synonymous with rockabilly and early rock n' roll. Available in nickel or gold covers and as sets or singles. Single conductor braided shield lead wire. Bridge Pickup: Rio Grande vintage tall boy Reverse wiring on the control plate with a Indian nickel on the volume pot. Will ship with a fender hard shell case. 7 day play guarantee when it arrives to your place. if your not satisfied with the guitar, ship it back to me and I’ll refund your purchase. Minus shipping. This is a killer instrument, but letting it go to take care of August rent.
Title: Fender Thinline Telecaster (MJT Part-caster)
